'''腸肝循環'''<ref>{{Cite book|chapter=Lipoproteins and Lipid Transport|title=Medical Biochemistry|url=http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/b978-0-323-05371-6.00018-8|publisher=Elsevier|date=2009|isbn=978-0-323-05371-6|pages=219–236|first=MH|last=Dominiczak}}</ref>（Enterohepatic circulation）是指[[胆汁酸|胆汁酸]]、[[胆红素|胆红素]]、藥物或其他物質在[[小腸|小腸]]和[[肝臟|肝臟]]之間的循環。這些被肝臟排出的物質（如：藥物）隨著肝臟分泌的[[膽汁|膽汁]]進入小腸，經消化道上皮細胞重新再吸收，進入人體。因此，腸肝循環會拉長某些藥物的[[半衰期|半生期]]。<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|title=Modeling Enterohepatic Circulation|url=http://link.springer.com/10.1007/s40495-017-0096-z|last=Okour|first=Malek|last2=Brundage|first2=Richard C.|date=2017-10-XX|journal=Current Pharmacology Reports|issue=5|doi=10.1007/s40495-017-0096-z|volume=3|pages=301–313|language=en|issn=2198-641X}}</ref>

腸肝循環是[[毒理学|毒理学]]中的重要主題之一，因為在腸肝循環過程中，若存在[[親脂性|親脂性]]的{{le|有害异物|xenobiotics}}，會造成反覆性的肝臟損傷。例如[[有机氯化合物|有機氯化合物]]，一旦攝入人體，就隨著腸肝循環代謝而不易排除；不過，近年來有些研究開始利用攝取腸道無法吸收的脂肪(例如[[奧利司他|奧利司他]])來協助將這些排入腸道的有機氯化合物隨糞便帶出體外。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Enterohepatic circulation of organochlorine compounds: a site for nutritional intervention|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/17296488|last=Jandacek|first=Ronald J.|last2=Tso|first2=Patrick|date=2007-03|journal=The Journal of Nutritional Biochemistry|issue=3|doi=10.1016/j.jnutbio.2006.12.001|volume=18|pages=163–167|issn=0955-2863|pmid=17296488}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The effect of olestra on the absorption, excretion and storage of 2,2',5,5' tetrachlorobiphenyl; 3,3',4,4' tetrachlorobiphenyl; and perfluorooctanoic acid|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19616301|last=Jandacek|first=R. J.|last2=Rider|first2=T.|date=2010-11|journal=Environment International|issue=8|doi=10.1016/j.envint.2009.06.010|volume=36|pages=880–883|issn=1873-6750|pmc=2891251|pmid=19616301|last3=Keller|first3=E. R.|last4=Tso|first4=P.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Reduction of the body burden of PCBs and DDE by dietary intervention in a randomized trial|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24629911|last=Jandacek|first=Ronald J.|last2=Heubi|first2=James E.|date=2014-04|journal=The Journal of Nutritional Biochemistry|issue=4|doi=10.1016/j.jnutbio.2014.01.002|volume=25|pages=483–488|issn=1873-4847|pmc=3960503|pmid=24629911|last3=Buckley|first3=Donna D.|last4=Khoury|first4=Jane C.|last5=Turner|first5=Wayman E.|last6=Sjödin|first6=Andreas|last7=Olson|first7=James R.|last8=Shelton|first8=Christie|last9=Helms|first9=Kim}}</ref>
